reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 12, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars A very good "Passive" Piezo Beeper
reviews.reviewText: If you are looking for a small "Passive" Piezo beeper, these work fine. A "Passive" beeper such as these acts much as a small speaker and must have a signal of some kind sent to it, as in a computer speaker. These will not work with DC voltages. A more commonly available "Active" Piezo beeper need only have a DC voltage applied and does not work well with signals.
Plug it and you can probably make any kind of computer you want. Gets you the POST error codes.
It is easy to install. And the red line should be connected to +5V pin.And when I turn on my desktop, it can make a short beep for me.
